			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Post your top bard issues here<a name="49809"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 6:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>So, our premiere class coorespondant <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/Forums/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=49800#49801">Tremelo </a>said that he's been searching for a list of current top issues for bards.
<br />

<br />
Since we haven't really compiled a list like this, I figured I'd start up a thread with my top issues, and hopefully other folks will use this as a place to post their own.
<br />

<br />
This should be a place for issues relevant to the bard class. Class-irrelevant issues like &quot;fix the collision system&quot; or &quot;add more raid/quest/solo content&quot; should be probably be posted over at www.everquestlive.com.
<br />

<br />
My top issues:
<br />

<br />
<b>Song pulses/song drops on the same server tick bug</b> - This is the issue where if a buff gets refreshed on the same server tick as it would have dropped, it drops anyway with a message like &quot;Your feet move faster. You slow down.&quot; How long have we had to live with this? It seems like it's gotten better recently but it still happens way too much.
<br />

<br />
<b>Bard fizzle rates</b> - I'd like to see this addressed two ways. First, I'd like to see a reduction of fizzle rates across all levels. The current idea is that a bard with max skills, 305 DEX,  and 305 CHA should see 5% fizzles. This sounds reasonable to me. However, I don't think this scales properly, and I think that bards with decent but lesser stats are seeing far too many fizzles. At the very minimum, the mesmerize line of songs needs to have a better fizzle modifier, because multiple fizzles on a single mezz can really be a liability when there are multiple adds.
<br />
Second, I'm not planning on purchasing the fizzle recovery AAs for a very long time because I've read and heard too many reports about how useless they are. This doesn't seem right to me. It seems like the highest fizzle recovery AA should recover all but a negligible number of fizzles.
<br />

<br />
Edit: Changed the name of the thread. I'm thinking it might be a good idea to gather the issues in one thread and do a Top Ten list in another thread. After there's been sufficient activity here I'll just do a nonscientific count and post the Top Ten in a new thread. So even if somebody else has already brought up your idea, post it anyway.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">"And now for my next miracle, I will turn water... into funk!"
</span></td>
