				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 10 Bard Issues (for Tremelo)<a name="49823"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 7:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I seem to be about the only one experiencing this post DX9 bug from a couple of patches ago.
<br />

<br />
Whenever I start a song or whenever it lands (3 seconds after the start), I get a hesitation in the graphics... about 0.2 seconds, I'd guess.
<br />

<br />
It's really easy to see this if you are looking at your character from  a 3rd person perspective while running in circles.  The effect is to make the animation jerky around starting and landing songs.
<br />

<br />
I have all spell effects turned off, logging turned off, old character models, 128 MB Nvidia GeForce4 Ti 4200, 1 GHz AMD Athlon, 768 MB DDR, cable modem.
<br />

<br />
This made being in a raid with a lot of people nearly unplayable.  With all melee and spell info from other players filtered out on the server side, it's much more playable, but still is not that good.
<br />

<br />
So these hesitations are coming from other players casting spells too.  I would see hesitations as long as 2 seconds while the raid was attacking a mob, and it would immediately smooth out after the mob died.
<br />

<br />
I have /bug'd this a couple of times, but have yet to see any fixes.
<br />

<br />
This is the bug I'd most like to see fixed.  Fizzles and song drops are minor, in my mind.
<br />
</span></td>
