				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 10 Bard Issues (for Tremelo)<a name="49889"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 3 04 7:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Casting Focus and Internal Metronome need to scale up properly in balance with their cost, and needs to take into consideration how often we cast compared to other classes. 47 AAs isnt it? I've stopped at Internal Metronome 3 or 4, because I've been told that level 5 has a miniscule, unnoticable improvement. A year and a half ago, Casting Focus 3 guaranteed no wrong notes. When that was the case, bards weren't overpowered. When that was &quot;fixed&quot;, we weren't refunded those AAs like we were our regen AAs during the infamous Mana Burn nerf patch.
<br />

<br />
When a song lands just as it was going to fade, the buff dissapears. This is especially problematic for AE resist songs which fade nearly 3 seconds early if you're lucky. Otherwise it fades just as the re pulse lands.
<br />

<br />

<br />
We need a more reliable way of invising a group across a dangerous area with mobs that don't see invis. Perhaps a song with 5 ticks of invis and a range of 90. 45 is entirely too small. Or an 'improved invis' song that just needs one pulse and lasts for 20 minutes, and has a 5 minute recast time.
<br />

<br />
Weapon procs need to not interfere with the spell casting bar.
<br />

<br />
Pathing needs to be fixed. I'm a bard, I pull, it's a bard problem. NPC's cant use a door 2 feet away from them. Instead, they walk into the wall for 12 seconds then warp onto me.
<br />

<br />
Autofollow. It should do what the name says. Just because someone is thrashing their hard drive for virtual memory doesn't mean autofollow should have them run in a circle, or suddenly change into autorun. Everyone always follows the bard.
<br />

<br />
Targetting needs to be fixed. I'm in Deepest Guk, I'm trying to pull, I click a frog, nothing happens..
<br />

<br />
I'd like to see an AA ability that makes my clicked effects last longer. My coldain ring, my Voice of the Serpent (clicking that every 8 minutes has really gotten old. In fact, just change that buff to 30 minutes.) Illusions too maybe? Ornate greaves? Epic/Prismatic Avatar proc? Songblade click?
<br />

<br />
Pet spells need to be able to be filtered off. With Spell Awareness and NPC spells filtered on, I see PC pets' spells. During raids it turns into terrible spam.
<br />

<br />
Our chants need to have their lure-like resist checks back. In PvP I have 500 resists and a ranger has 300. I debuff him with Jam Fest 3, 4.2 percussion Harmony of Sound, and still, I cant bellow, mez, or snare him. But he can nuke me through my 500 resists. And this is just a ranger nuke, dont even bring up dueling a wizard in a smaller sized arena.
<br />

<br />
The description for Jam Fest needs to be changed. It's awful. Same with Fleet of Foot, if that even does ANYthing.
<br />

<br />
The newer drum models need to be totally redone. They're WAY too huge for any class, clipping into a hip in the secondary slot. Primary slot drums and lutes dont make any sense during the animation of playing them.
<br />

<br />
And finally going back to songs fading as they land, I think there is more to that problem than just the direct bug. In my opinion there should be a more fundemental change, where songs have either a shorter casting time, like 2.8 seconds, or should last longer than the intended 12 seconds. Perhaps it could be an AA ability. Or what if all the 2 tick songs lasted 4 ticks, but you can only recieve 4 songs from a single bard. If a 5th song is attempted, it's either blocked or it overwrites the first song. I'm in no way lazy, I fully intend to sing 4 songs when Im twisting, but I think it's rediculous that I have to play EQ in 3 second intervals, and suffer from Carpel Tunnel a few years earlier than scheduled.
<br />

<br />
Guess I'm out of ideas for now. :P</span></td>
