				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, some of the things mentioned above aren't bard issues and are just bard wants (we need better buffs? FM not powerful enough?). Others are bugs that aren't bard-specific (DX9). I'm not saying these aren't important to some people, but we're trying to make a list a bard problems. The biggest issues/bugs for me are:
<br />

<br />
Issue: Missed notes even with maxed AA's. (parses show ~6% missed notes with 57 AAs spent in fizzle reduction). Since we cast every three seconds for hours on end. Missed notes become very noticable.
<br />

<br />
Bug: &quot;Your feet move faster.&quot; &quot;You slow down.&quot; Always a nuisance, and at other times it can be fatal.
<br />

<br />
Bug: Procs making our casting bar disappear. Mostly annoying as I know most bards develop a 3 second counter in their head and know when their spells are going to go off. But the problem with this is that it can be hard to distinguish between this bug, a missed note and a stun/interrupt.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I think part of the problem with coming up with a list like this is that many bards are pretty content with their class. If you ask a cleric or a warrior what their class issues are, you could be there a long time listening to their problems.</span></td>
