				<td colspan="2"><span>Casting bar doesn't disappear on some procs but definitely does on others.  My Stave of Slavers kills it every time it procs.  I don't rely on it but I know many do so this is a problem.  I agree that a 5% fizzle rate is probably too high as it now stands.  Think about this -- we probably don't have much more than that already.  On raids, my dex is maxed, my cha is in the upper 200s and my skills have been maxed for ages.  If you fizzle once every 20 song tries, that's about once per mob on raids or in tough zones on XP fights and that's pretty close to normal for me with those buffs.  And it is still annoying.   Most casters launch 4 or 5 spells in a fight.  Bards start 15 to 20 songs in that time period.  5% for both regular casters and for us, given the very temporary nature of our song effects, penalizes us much more. Let me elaborate slightly -- let's say the average duration of a caster's buff spell is 1 hour.  The average duration of a buff song is 18 seconds. (I'm being very generous to the devs with these assumptions, too).  That means our buffs last, on the average, around 1/200 or .5% of the duration of caster buffs.  Which means they suffer 1 fizzle for every 20 hours of buffage while we suffer 1 fizzle for every 7 minutes of buffage.  And that is fudging the numbers tremendously in the direction of equality.  Reality is going to be even worse.</span></td>
